channel.title: I've created a new band
channel.description:
Well, good evening gentlemen and ladies. Well, I'm pretty excited, and figured I'd post here about my news. Recently, I've had the pleasure of being invited into a band. They're a grunge/punk/rock band, and we've started about two weeks ago. Currently, we've been working on two songs. One, called Downwards Spiral, is a little on the unfinished side, and the other, which for now is called Untitled Finale, is a little more polished.
Neither of the songs have lyrics yet, as we're still testing out our "sound". I'm the bands drummer, and so far, I think I've done well. I'm 17, live in Parma, Ohio, and the band is Secrets of a Hollow Earth.
As I said, I'm 17, the guitarists are 18/19 respectively, and our bassist is 21. We're all passionate about music, and we've all been playing since we were children (albeit, not together, and nowhere near as organized).
Be aware that I've been arranging as well as tweaking the music itself, so it's not a true representation of our skills.
A picture of me, taken last night at 3 AM, trying to grind out some fillers...that sucked. Horribly. :jizz:
![](upload://6I6PuuEmauXO02up6hgyYXrei26.jpeg)
The music I've so far arranged and tweaked can be found here-in;
Untitled: [url]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W2NfEizHU5A[/url]
Downwards Spiral: [url]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MXKZGHfJjKw[/url]
None of it is really finished, but if any of you have input on where to take it from here, possible voice-sound-alikes that would fit the music, or anyone feels like taking the reins on writing some lyrics (with credit, of course), please, feel free to poke your head in.
EDIT: Name of the band changed courtesy of "hercule poirots nutsack". +1 rep.
